Count 2 - Disorderly conduct (DVO) - No contest plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, battery (DVO).  Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Maintain full-time employment,schooling, combination;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Attend Batterer's treatment program;
4) Provide DNA sample;
5) Spend three (3) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 02-04-16 by 5:00 p.m.
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Minutes.
